  <discussion>Mammillaria pottsii superficially resembles Coryphantha subgen. Escobaria: the erect cylindric stems are totally concealed by short, pale gray or ashy white spines. In M. pottsii, the ring of reproductive structures (flowers or fruits) encircles the stem two centimeters or more below the stem apex, unlike the apical flowers and fruits of most coryphanthas.</discussion>
